Design Amazon Locker 

Design Airline Management System 

⭐ Payment & Finance Domain (very common) 

Design Wallet System 

Design UPI/Payment Gateway 

Design Expense Tracker 

⭐ Concurrency-Focused LLD 

Design Thread Pool 

Design Blocking Queue 

Design Pub/Sub Framework 

Reader‑Writer Lock 

Producer‑Consumer 

 

📍 6. Databases in LLD 

Even in LLD, you must show you understand storage. 

Learn: 

Basic schema design 

Normalization 

Mapping classes to DB tables 

Repositories (DAO layer) 

Transaction handling (ACID basics) 

 

📍 7. API Design Basics 

Companies will expect you to show: 

Request/response modeling 

DTOs vs Entities 

Validation 

Versioning 

Pagination, filtering 

 

📍 8. Clean Code & Best Practices 

Very important for top companies. 

Meaningful class naming 

Designing extensible code 

Handling edge cases 

Avoiding God classes 

Proper package structure 

 

📍 9. Testing Fundamentals 

You must show awareness of testing: 

Unit testing 

Mocking 

Testable class structure 

Dependency injection 

 

📍 10. End‑to‑End LLD Practice 

Mock complete designs including: 

Requirements clarification 

Functional & non‑functional requirements 

Class diagram 

Sequence diagram 

Class definitions 

Design pattern justification 

Trade-offs 

 

🎯 How to Prepare (Roadmap) 

Week 1 → OOP + SOLID 

Week 2 → Design Patterns 

Week 3 → UML + class modeling 

Week 4 → LLD problems (Parking lot, Elevator, Splitwise) 

Week 5 → High‑quality coding + concurrency 

 
